Please let me know if that is fine with you.   A few other quick things:   1)	All of the current ?Average Calculation? work is in QA, not QA4. There have been updates to some of the code that we updated in QA in QA4 so we will need to bring our code over to QA4 and make sure that we are not impacting the current code in QA4 at all. That is why this is listed below with some additional time. 2)	As I mentioned, I am out Wednesday afternoon until the following Wednesday. Ariel is aware of all of the components to be created/updated and I will touch base with Jim to make sure he is up to speed in case Ariel has any questions/concerns. 3)	Currently, we have 20 hours left in our current SOW. We have three estimates, two of which we reviewed Friday, and one new one below:  a.	Next Order Calculations (30 hours) b.	VF Pages (42 hours) c.	CSV Logic (70 hours)   Please let me know how you would like to proceed and we can work from there. Thanks Chris and estimate below on the ?Next Order Calculations?:   Next Order Calculations: (30 hours total) 1.	Highest consumption (fields Avg. 7, 14, or 30) / Strips on hand (6 hours) i.	Have Trigger go 10 days prior to the estimated run out date ii.	Example 50 Strips on hand / Highest Consumption (Avg # is 1.8, DO NOT Round) a.	Would have a value here of 27.7 (take the shortest option of days, here would be 27) and we would send the alert 10 days prior to estimated run out date 2.	Update the rounding from the current batch i.	Create formula fields to round the current values (Test Range (7 Days), 14, 30 (3 fields) 3.	Alert when the 10 day has come: i.	Option 1 create a Case on the Person Account (Patient) (4 hours) a.	Assign the Case to "Patient Reorder Case Queue" 1.	Create this Case Queue b.	Case subject "Potential Reorder" 1.	Create this value in the Case subject dropdown c.	Category "Potential Reorder 1.	Create this value in the Category dropdown ii.	Option 2 create an Opportunity for "Automatic Refill" (6 hours) a.	Dependent picklist for (30, 60, 90 day shipment). Each are options (3 total) b.	Will Lancets be included? 1.	Yes 2.	No c.	Opportunity Name: SET d.	Close Date: Today() e.	Stage: Ready to Process f.	Type: Re-order g.	Method of Shipment: USPS 1.	Create new value h.	Create related Opportunity Product(s) 1.	Product Name: Telcare Glucose Test Strips (50 ct) 2.	Quantity: Run Rate (# of Test Strips used each day, actual value) * day selected in Day Refill Period i.	2 Strips per day * 30 day refill period = 60 / 50 (# of Test Strips) = 1.2 (Dependent on which average? 7, 14 or 30 day?) ii.	Round the value up to the next whole number iii.	In this example the Quantity would be set as 2 3.	Sales Price: Defaulted value from the Pricebook i.	Create 2nd related Opportunity Product if "Lancet Required" Question is "true" 1.	Products Name: TL001 (Grab product name) 2.	Quantity: # of Telcare Glucose Test Strips (50 ct) / 2 i.	Example: Order is for Quantity of 4 Test Strips, we would the Lancet Product with a Quantity of 1 ii.	We do NOT round up, we round down to the nearest whole number. Customer has 3 ordered a quantity of 3 Test Strips (150 total), we still include 1 Lancet Product  iii.	Option 3 flag a new field on the Account and then this will appear in the report (6 hours) a.	Create a new checkbox field on the Account for "Automatic Refill" and set this value to true if we are at 10 days or less b.	Create a new "Date/Time" report setting NOW() in this value when this field is set to true c.	When a Opportunity with the type of "Reorder" is created and related to this Person Account, and the Closed Won date is after the newly created Date field, then we will set the "Date/Time" to false and the "Automatic Refill" box to false d.	Create a basic Program with the specific Partner Program and the field is "True" 1.	Create a distribution list for this report   Bring over and merge all components from QA to QA4: 4 hours New/updated components: 22 hours QA/Deployment: 4 hours   Total: 30 hours

Accenture asked me to architect out a solution prior to the meeting and working with Patrick, I put together a straw man of enabling solutions based on some lambda?s that will run every minute against their existing Dynamo DB on Amazon.
